snippet: The interim president of Ukraine said roadblocks were being set up around Kiev, the capital, because of fears of provocation during a holiday later in the week.
abstract: Ukrainian security forces and antigovernment rebels clash on the edges of rebel-controlled Slovyansk; acting Pres Oleksandr V Turchynov says roadblocks are being set up around capital of Kiev because of fears of disturbances or violence during upcoming emotionally charged holiday celebrating victory over Nazis in World War II.

byline.original: By C. J. CHIVERS and NOAH SNEIDER
byline.contributor: Andrew E. Kramer contributed reporting from Odessa, Ukraine; David M. Herszenhorn from Kiev, Ukraine; and Alan Cowell from London.

lead_paragraph: The interim president of Ukraine said roadblocks were being set up around Kiev, the capital, because of fears of provocation during a holiday later in the week.

headline.main: Deadly Clashes Erupt in Ukraine as Troops Push Toward a Rebel-Held City
headline.print_headline: Deadly Clashes Erupt in Ukraine as Troops Push Toward a Rebel-Held City
